#. <section class="sutta" id="an4.37"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.37:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.37:0.2"
msgid "4. Cakkavagga"
msgstr "4. Situations"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.37:0.3"
msgid "37. Aparihāniyasutta"
msgstr "37. Non-decline"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an4.37:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu abhabbo parihānāya "
"nibbānasseva santike."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, a mendicant who has four qualities can’t decline, and is close "
"to extinguishment."

msgctxt "an4.37:1.2"
msgid "Katamehi catūhi?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "an4.37:1.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlasampanno hoti, indriyesu guttadvāro hoti, "
"bhojane mattaññū hoti, jāgariyaṃ anuyutto hoti."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant is accomplished in ethics, guards the sense doors, eats in "
"moderation, and is dedicated to wakefulness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an4.37:2.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlasampanno hoti?"
msgstr "And how is a mendicant accomplished in ethics?"

msgctxt "an4.37:2.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlavā hoti pātimokkhasaṃvarasaṃvuto viharati "
"ācāragocarasampanno aṇumattesu vajjesu bhayadassāvī, samādāya sikkhati "
"sikkhāpadesu."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant is ethical, restrained in the monastic code, and "
"accomplished in appropriate behavior and means of collecting alms. Seeing "
"danger in the slightest fault, they keep the rules they’ve undertaken."

msgctxt "an4.37:2.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlasampanno hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is accomplished in ethics."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.40"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an4.37:3.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu indriyesu guttadvāro hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant guard the sense doors?"

msgctxt "an4.37:3.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā na nimittaggāhī hoti "
"nānubyañjanaggāhī."
msgstr ""
"When a mendicant sees a sight with their eyes, they don’t get caught up in "
"the features and details."

msgctxt "an4.37:3.3"
msgid ""
"Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ cakkhundriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā "
"pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ, tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati; rakkhati "
"cakkhundriyaṃ; cakkhundriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati."
msgstr ""
"If the faculty of sight were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of "
"desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they "
"practice restraint, protecting the faculty of sight, and achieving restraint "
"over it."

msgctxt "an4.37:3.4"
msgid "Sotena saddaṃ sutvā … "
msgstr "Hearing a sound with their ears … "

msgctxt "an4.37:3.5"
msgid "ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā … "
msgstr "Smelling an odor with their nose … "

msgctxt "an4.37:3.6"
msgid "jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā … "
msgstr "Tasting a flavor with their tongue … "

msgctxt "an4.37:3.7"
msgid "kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā … "
msgstr "Feeling a touch with their body … "

msgctxt "an4.37:3.8"
msgid "manasā dhammaṃ viññāya na nimittaggāhī hoti nānubyañjanaggāhī."
msgstr ""
"Knowing a thought with their mind, they don’t get caught up in the features "
"and details."

msgctxt "an4.37:3.9"
msgid ""
"Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ manindriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā "
"pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ, tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati; rakkhati "
"manindriyaṃ; manindriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati."
msgstr ""
"If the faculty of mind were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of "
"desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they "
"practice restraint, protecting the faculty of mind, and achieving restraint "
"over it."

msgctxt "an4.37:3.10"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu indriyesu guttadvāro hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant guards the sense doors."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an4.37:4.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu bhojane mattaññū hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant eat in moderation?"

msgctxt "an4.37:4.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu paṭisaṅkhā yoniso āhāraṃ āhāreti:"
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant reflects properly on the food that they eat:"

msgctxt "an4.37:4.3"
msgid ""
"‘neva davāya na madāya na maṇḍanāya na vibhūsanāya; yāvadeva imassa kāyassa "
"ṭhitiyā yāpanāya vihiṃsūparatiyā brahmacariyānuggahāya. Iti purāṇañca "
"vedanaṃ paṭihaṅkhāmi, navañca vedanaṃ na uppādessāmi, yātrā ca me "
"bhavissati, anavajjatā ca phāsuvihāro cā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Not for fun, indulgence, adornment, or decoration, but only to continue and "
"sustain this body, avoid harm, and support spiritual practice. So that I "
"will put an end to old discomfort and not give rise to new discomfort, and "
"so that I will keep on living blamelessly and at ease.’"

msgctxt "an4.37:4.4"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu bhojane mattaññū hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant eats in moderation."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an4.37:5.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu jāgariyaṃ anuyutto hoti?"
msgstr "And how is a mendicant dedicated to wakefulness?"

msgctxt "an4.37:5.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu divasaṃ caṅkamena nisajjāya āvaraṇīyehi dhammehi "
"cittaṃ parisodheti;"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant practices walking and sitting meditation by day, "
"purifying their mind from obstacles."

msgctxt "an4.37:5.3"
msgid ""
"rattiyā paṭhamaṃ yāmaṃ caṅkamena nisajjāya āvaraṇīyehi dhammehi cittaṃ "
"parisodheti;"
msgstr ""
"In the evening, they continue to practice walking and sitting meditation."

msgctxt "an4.37:5.4"
msgid ""
"rattiyā majjhimaṃ yāmaṃ dakkhiṇena passena sīhaseyyaṃ kappeti, pāde pādaṃ "
"accādhāya, sato sampajāno uṭṭhānasaññaṃ manasi karitvā;"
msgstr ""
"In the middle of the night, they lie down in the lion’s posture—on the right "
"side, placing one foot on top of the other—mindful and aware, and focused on "
"the time of getting up."

msgctxt "an4.37:5.5"
msgid ""
"rattiyā pacchimaṃ yāmaṃ paccuṭṭhāya caṅkamena nisajjāya āvaraṇīyehi dhammehi "
"cittaṃ parisodheti."
msgstr ""
"In the last part of the night, they get up and continue to practice walking "
"and sitting meditation, purifying their mind from obstacles."

msgctxt "an4.37:5.6"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu jāgariyaṃ anuyutto hoti."
msgstr "This is how a mendicant is dedicated to wakefulness."

msgctxt "an4.37:5.7"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu abhabbo "
"parihānāya, nibbānasseva santiketi."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant who has these four qualities can’t decline, and has drawn near "
"to extinguishment."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an4.37:6.1"
msgid "Sīle patiṭṭhito bhikkhu,"
msgstr "Established in ethics,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.37:6.2"
msgid "indriyesu ca saṃvuto;"
msgstr "restrained in the sense faculties,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.37:6.3"
msgid "Bhojanamhi ca mattaññū,"
msgstr "eating in moderation,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.37:6.4"
msgid "jāgariyaṃ anuyuñjati."
msgstr "and dedicated to wakefulness;"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an4.37:7.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vihārī ātāpī,"
msgstr "a mendicant lives like this, with keen energy,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.37:7.2"
msgid "ahorattamatandito;"
msgstr "tireless all night and day,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.37:7.3"
msgid "Bhāvayaṃ kusalaṃ dhammaṃ,"
msgstr "developing skillful qualities,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.37:7.4"
msgid "yogakkhemassa pattiyā."
msgstr "in order to find sanctuary."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an4.37:8.1"
msgid "Appamādarato bhikkhu,"
msgstr "A mendicant who loves to be diligent,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: bhayadassi vā → bhayadassīvā (pts1) | bhayadassāvī (mr)
msgctxt "an4.37:8.2"
msgid "pamāde bhayadassi vā;"
msgstr "seeing fear in negligence,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.37:8.3"
msgid "Abhabbo parihānāya,"
msgstr "can’t decline,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.37:8.4"
msgid "nibbānasseva santike”ti."
msgstr "and has drawn near to extinguishment.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.37:8.5"
msgid "Sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
